About me 

I am pursuing my MS in Electronics Engineering at Yeungnam University under Prof. Kim Sungho in AVIL lab (Advanced Visual Intelligence Lab). I am a first year MS student and one of the GKS scholars in 2021. Currently, my research domain is spinning around computer vision and deep learning.

I have earned my Bachelor's degree in 2021 from Narula Institute of Technology (NiT) under WBUT in Electronics and Instrumentation Engineering. In my early B.Tech, I have done few research on Geoscience under Dr. Dibyendu Sur and afterwards I have done projects and research with Prof. Bansari Deb Majumdar and Ms. Susumita Das in Biomedical Engineering, Machine Learning and Automation. I have worked as a research intern in DRDO, DRL under Scientist Dhiraj Dutta.

Projects

  • Deepfake related project [ Currently ongoing, will be releasing the details later ]

  • Project from ETRI, South Korea : Pose estimation from Point cloud [Ongoing]

  • Project from 3D Automation and RIS, Korea  : Collaboration project with my fellow lab member on AR/VR [Ongoing]

  • Project from PHA, Korea  : Collaboration project with my fellow lab member on Object detection and Classification [Ongoing]

Challenge : The objects are too similar to differentiate.

  • Project from 3D Automation, Korea : Collaboration project with lab members on automated distance and angle detection and overlaying 3D ArUco marker in real world.

Challenge : Camera calibration was not a challenge but calibrating it properly was a challenge, ArUco marker's features are great but till a certain distance but few changes in the ratio of size and distance solved the issue.

  • Individual project  : Spectral unmixing for hyperspectral image

Challenge : Hyperspectral image consists of mixed pixels so to divide them into different pure pixels is hard and a big time challenge. So, acquiring endmembers was a bit challenging at first

  • Individual project : Black ice detection using hyperspectral imaging system 

Challenge : Hyperspectral image holds abundant amount of information so, the preprocessing also needed more patience compared to a RGB image. 

  • Undergrad project : Automated soil's water level and moisture detection 

  • Undergrad project : Smart cattle area using Piezo electric sensor
